WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:03.002
Announcer:
You're watching second chance.

00:03.004 --> 00:04.870
What we're about to do
should be left to god.

00:04.872 --> 00:08.807
Catch all-new episodes
wednesdays and check out
our other fox programs--

00:08.809 --> 00:11.310
Rosewood, bones <i>and</i> lucifer.

00:11.312 --> 00:13.145
-What's your name?
-Lucifer.

00:13.147 --> 00:14.313
Like the devil?

00:14.315 --> 00:15.748
Only on fox.

00:16.950 --> 00:19.018
<i>Previously</i>
<i>on "second chance"...</i>

00:19.020 --> 00:20.853
Woman: Disgraced sheriff
jimmy pritchard

00:20.855 --> 00:22.054
Took his own life today.

00:23.857 --> 00:26.191
You're the first to journey
all the way back --

00:26.193 --> 00:27.559
To get another chance.

00:27.561 --> 00:30.863
James: I know you. You're one of
those rich computer twins.

00:30.865 --> 00:32.498
Otto re-coded
your white blood cells

00:32.500 --> 00:33.999
To fight the cancer
in my blood.

00:34.001 --> 00:36.702
You brought me back
to save you.

00:36.704 --> 00:39.538
Otto:
He's stronger than predicted.

00:42.709 --> 00:45.044
Why does he think
he's my father?

00:45.046 --> 00:46.311
Because he is.

00:48.081 --> 00:51.016
He should never have called you
an idiot, your dad.

00:51.018 --> 00:52.851
You just try to see
the best in people.

00:52.853 --> 00:53.986
I saw the best in my dad,

00:53.988 --> 00:55.988
Even if he didn't see it
in himself.

00:55.990 --> 00:57.523
You know,
I'm glad you're here.

00:57.525 --> 00:58.857
My dad's done so much
by himself.

00:58.859 --> 01:00.059
He really needs you.

01:00.061 --> 01:02.394
Can you just promise me
you're here to help him?

01:02.396 --> 01:03.896
I'm not a monkey
that jumps

01:03.898 --> 01:05.731
Every time
you say "solve a puzzle."

01:05.733 --> 01:07.666
[ speaking in twinspeak ]

01:07.668 --> 01:09.668
Otto!

01:09.670 --> 01:11.103
I just want to know...

01:11.105 --> 01:12.871
What you said to me then...

01:12.873 --> 01:15.340
I will always be here
with you, otto.

01:15.342 --> 01:16.809
...Is it still true?

01:20.547 --> 01:22.548
[ police radio chatter ]

01:22.550 --> 01:25.284
I'm looking
right at them.

01:25.286 --> 01:28.620
Six, right out on the street
this time.

01:28.622 --> 01:32.424
Reese and his jalisco brothers
won this round.

01:32.426 --> 01:34.927
Chan is m.I.A.

01:34.929 --> 01:37.062
This turf war
is escalating.

01:37.064 --> 01:38.597
Hey.

01:38.599 --> 01:40.766
-Hey.
[ phone beeps ]

01:40.768 --> 01:44.203
These six
were chan lee's bodyguards.

01:44.205 --> 01:48.941
Lee entered the seattle
heroin market just a month ago.

01:48.943 --> 01:51.143
D.C.'s leaning on me
to clean this mess up.

01:51.145 --> 01:52.911
The doctor
wants some good news,

01:52.913 --> 01:55.647
So I want you to work this
until you can get me some.

01:59.752 --> 02:02.554
Father and son
on their way home.

02:02.556 --> 02:03.455
[ sighs ]

02:03.457 --> 02:04.723
Wrong place, wrong time.

02:04.725 --> 02:05.791
Woman: No, please!

02:09.295 --> 02:11.063
No!

02:11.065 --> 02:12.431
<i>Man: Tragedy struck today</i>

02:12.433 --> 02:14.466
<i>In this working-class</i>
<i>west seattle neighborhood</i>

02:14.468 --> 02:16.602
<i>As a drug war exploded</i>
<i>in a violent shootout.</i>

02:16.604 --> 02:19.471
<i>Local police along with fbi</i>
<i>are trying to find out</i>

02:19.473 --> 02:22.007
<i>Exactly who's behind</i>
<i>this spike in drug violence</i>

02:22.009 --> 02:23.642
<i>Over the last six weeks.</i>

02:23.644 --> 02:26.278
<i>It is believed to be a dispute</i>
<i>between rival gangs competing</i>

02:26.280 --> 02:28.180
<i>-Over the local heroin market.</i>
<i>[ ringing ]</i>

02:28.182 --> 02:30.516
[ cellphone vibrating ]

02:30.518 --> 02:32.251
James: Duval.

02:34.687 --> 02:37.422
Duval,
I know you can hear me.

02:37.424 --> 02:38.423
Duval.

02:38.425 --> 02:40.325
How many times
do I have to tell you?

02:40.327 --> 02:41.994
Stop using
that lookinglass tech

02:41.996 --> 02:43.829
To make my phone
answer your calls.

02:43.831 --> 02:45.164
This is important.

02:45.166 --> 02:47.499
I'm in the middle
of a drug-fueled gang war

02:47.501 --> 02:48.634
Trying to figure out

02:48.636 --> 02:51.003
Who's putting all this heroin
on my streets.

02:51.005 --> 02:52.271
I think I did.

02:52.273 --> 02:53.305
Did what?

02:53.307 --> 02:55.974
Put all the heroin
on your streets.

02:55.976 --> 02:57.442
Just meet me at peng's.

02:57.444 --> 03:00.012
Not until you tell me
what this is about.

03:00.014 --> 03:02.681
[ receiver clicks ]

03:02.683 --> 03:04.750
[ siren wailing ]

03:11.191 --> 03:13.525
[ muffled grunting ]

03:13.527 --> 03:14.693
What did we tell you?

03:14.695 --> 03:16.795
You should've stayed
out of seattle.

03:16.797 --> 03:18.530
You want turkey
or roast beef?

03:18.532 --> 03:19.665
Roast beef.

03:19.667 --> 03:21.733
[ grunting continues ]

03:27.540 --> 03:29.474
[ muffled screams ]

03:32.145 --> 03:34.179
[ sighs ]

03:34.181 --> 03:36.515
You've got one minute,
starting now.

03:36.517 --> 03:40.085
Duval, sit down, please.

03:46.593 --> 03:47.893
[ sighs ]

03:47.895 --> 03:51.029
1990, there's a flood of heroin
on the streets.

03:51.031 --> 03:54.099
Worse than now --
more blood, more drugs.

03:54.101 --> 03:56.268
Guy running it
was a guy named ray carson.

03:56.270 --> 03:58.570
I remember that.
You rolled up his operation.

03:58.572 --> 04:00.405
Put a dozen of his guys
behind bars,

04:00.407 --> 04:01.540
But carson got away.

04:01.542 --> 04:04.042
He didn't get away,
but I'll get to that.

04:04.044 --> 04:06.578
Now, before it all went down,
I had a c.I.

04:06.580 --> 04:09.781
Ray's girlfriend,
joan solodar.

04:09.783 --> 04:12.884
Joan solodar
from solodar motors?
Yeah.

04:12.886 --> 04:15.254
Who sponsored little league
teams and school fairs?

04:15.256 --> 04:16.521
She was your c.I.?

04:16.523 --> 04:18.056
That's who she is now.

04:18.058 --> 04:21.693
Back then, I saw a good girl
in a bad situation.

04:21.695 --> 04:24.196
I was gonna stop the drug war
and get her out.

04:24.198 --> 04:25.931
One night, she calls me,

04:25.933 --> 04:29.101
Says ray found out
she was working for me,

04:29.103 --> 04:30.702
Started beating her.

04:30.704 --> 04:32.004
She shot him.

04:33.806 --> 04:35.374
He knew it, jimmy.

04:35.376 --> 04:38.043
He knew
I was working for you.

04:39.912 --> 04:42.614
Official story
was that ray got away.

04:42.616 --> 04:44.316
You covered up
a homicide.

04:44.318 --> 04:47.052
I rolled up the biggest
drug source in seattle.

04:47.054 --> 04:48.987
I gave a young woman
a new life.

04:48.989 --> 04:51.123
She swore to me
she'd go straight.

04:51.125 --> 04:52.958
For 20 years,
I believed her.

04:52.960 --> 04:55.427
I watched her build
her business,

04:55.429 --> 04:57.963
Raise her profile
in the community.

04:57.965 --> 05:00.132
What happened
after 20 years?

05:00.134 --> 05:02.901
I won big
in a high-stakes poker game.

05:02.903 --> 05:05.971
We played all night.
I hit every hand.

05:05.973 --> 05:07.806
Cory just kept losing.

05:07.808 --> 05:09.141
Cory?

05:09.143 --> 05:10.609
This harvard
m.B.A. Hotshot.

05:10.611 --> 05:12.311
Works in
an accounting firm uptown.

05:12.313 --> 05:14.813
I'm little short,
jimmy, again.

05:14.815 --> 05:15.947
I'm on a losing streak.

05:15.949 --> 05:17.783
I don't know what's wrong
with me.

05:17.785 --> 05:19.851
All that crap
you're putting up your nose.

05:19.853 --> 05:24.323
You know what, cory?
You can't play here anymore.

05:24.325 --> 05:26.291
I got to tell
your other games, too.

05:26.293 --> 05:27.359
Please, please.

05:27.361 --> 05:29.328
No, no, come on, please.
Don't cut me off.

05:29.330 --> 05:30.529
I got some information.

05:30.531 --> 05:32.798
All right, maybe it's worth
what I owe you.

05:32.800 --> 05:35.767
I know who's behind
all the heroin in seattle.

05:36.869 --> 05:38.337
It's an old girlfriend
of yours.

05:38.339 --> 05:39.805
You know,
the one who sells cars.

05:39.807 --> 05:41.006
That's a lie.

05:41.008 --> 05:43.008
Listen, my -- my firm
put me on the account.

05:43.010 --> 05:44.810
I'm the one
running the audit.

05:44.812 --> 05:49.114
She's laundering the money
through her car dealerships.

05:49.116 --> 05:51.516
She's running smack,
jimmy.

05:51.518 --> 05:55.120
I didn't
want to believe him.

05:55.122 --> 05:58.490
So, what did you do?

05:58.492 --> 06:00.459
Joan:
Well, as I live and breathe.

06:00.461 --> 06:03.528
Has it been
two years already?

06:03.530 --> 06:07.132
I had a good night
at poker, solly.

06:07.134 --> 06:09.868
Thought I'd pick up
my new car early.

06:09.870 --> 06:11.069
Solly.

06:11.071 --> 06:14.039
You know you're the only one
who still calls me that?

06:14.041 --> 06:15.640
We go back.

06:15.642 --> 06:17.442
Yes, we do, sheriff.

06:18.978 --> 06:20.278
Let's go to my office.

06:23.850 --> 06:25.584
Why'd you close
the door, jimmy?

06:25.586 --> 06:27.319
I've been
hearing things, joan,

06:27.321 --> 06:29.988
About you dealing smack.

06:29.990 --> 06:33.325
Let me see your books.
Show me it's all legal.

06:33.327 --> 06:36.762
Listen, sheriff...

06:36.764 --> 06:41.500
You saved my life back then,
and I will never forget that.

06:41.502 --> 06:44.069
I covered up a murder
for you!

06:44.071 --> 06:47.406
You did.

06:50.109 --> 06:52.144
Show me the books, joan.

06:56.783 --> 06:59.217
You know I can't do that,
sheriff.

06:59.219 --> 07:01.386
Lenny.

07:01.388 --> 07:04.856
Last thing you want
is your fed son

07:04.858 --> 07:08.026
Finding out
about what we did together.

07:08.028 --> 07:11.263
Don't open a door unless
you're ready to walk through it.

07:14.300 --> 07:18.937
I must've dialed your number
10 times after that.

07:18.939 --> 07:21.039
I hung up every time.

07:23.075 --> 07:25.010
But I'm telling you now.

07:28.714 --> 07:32.284
Well, I'm glad it only took you
coming back from the dead

07:32.286 --> 07:34.619
To make you finally
see the light.

07:34.621 --> 07:37.889
But you know I need evidence
to take to the bureau,

07:37.891 --> 07:39.324
And you never got any.

07:39.326 --> 07:40.158
I have a plan.

07:40.160 --> 07:40.992
A plan?

07:40.994 --> 07:42.627
Yeah.
I go to joan as a buyer.

07:42.629 --> 07:44.963
Once we have a deal,
you come in with the bureau.

07:44.965 --> 07:47.599
Stop the drugs,
stop the killing.

07:47.601 --> 07:49.801
I know her, duval.

07:49.803 --> 07:51.803
She thinks I'm dead.

07:51.805 --> 07:54.105
She won't see me coming.

07:54.107 --> 07:55.440
Joan: That's good.

07:55.442 --> 07:56.975
[ <i>muffled screaming</i> ]

07:56.977 --> 07:59.678
Really nice work.

07:59.680 --> 08:01.680
Thank you.

08:03.916 --> 08:05.851
Send that to hong kong.

08:05.853 --> 08:07.986
Make sure they know
this is my town

08:07.988 --> 08:10.322
And I'm the only one
who sells in it.

08:19.832 --> 08:24.169
â™ª

08:24.171 --> 08:25.403
[ door opens ]

08:28.708 --> 08:29.808
Too loud?

08:29.810 --> 08:30.809
Yeah.

08:30.811 --> 08:33.144
Uh, maybe just --
just a little.

08:33.146 --> 08:34.179
Yeah, sorry.

08:34.181 --> 08:35.814
It, uh,
it just kept sounding better

08:35.816 --> 08:37.349
-The louder we turned it.
-Mm-hmm.

08:37.351 --> 08:39.618
Garret says that it's meant
to be played loud.
Oh.

08:39.620 --> 08:41.019
So...

08:41.021 --> 08:42.721
You must be garret.

08:42.723 --> 08:44.456
Yeah.
Yeah, this is garret.

08:44.458 --> 08:46.324
Garret,
this is my aunt helen.

08:46.326 --> 08:49.127
Nice to meet you,
my aunt helen.

08:49.129 --> 08:52.063
You can call me helen.

08:52.065 --> 08:55.967
So, how do you two,
uh, know each other?

08:55.969 --> 08:57.502
Oh, we met at school.

08:57.504 --> 08:58.537
Oh.

08:58.539 --> 08:59.538
You're in high school?

08:59.540 --> 09:03.041
Uh, no, garret is 20.

09:03.043 --> 09:05.410
Which is older.

09:05.412 --> 09:09.548
So, in college?

09:09.550 --> 09:12.384
Taking a gap year.

09:12.386 --> 09:14.553
His band
played the dance.

09:14.555 --> 09:16.054
Garret is a drummer.

09:16.056 --> 09:18.056
Can he stay
for dinner?

09:18.058 --> 09:20.892
[ chuckles ]

09:20.894 --> 09:24.996
â™ª

09:27.166 --> 09:29.968
Go on home.

09:33.573 --> 09:37.142
Don't open the door unless
you're ready to walk through it.

09:41.013 --> 09:44.749
How you doing?
I'm lenny.

09:44.751 --> 09:46.017
Cameron brown.

09:46.019 --> 09:48.386
Came here to buy a car,
but if this is your handshake,

09:48.388 --> 09:50.255
Then I'm not sure
we could do business.

09:51.223 --> 09:54.259
Oh, why don't we show you
some cars?

09:54.261 --> 09:55.427
Come on, lenny.

09:55.429 --> 09:57.295
My granddaughter's got
a stronger grip than this.

09:57.297 --> 09:59.531
Your granddaughter?

09:59.533 --> 10:01.199
Did you --

10:01.201 --> 10:02.367
<i>Did you just say</i>
<i>your granddaughter?</i>

10:02.369 --> 10:04.035
James,
given your current age,

10:04.037 --> 10:07.072
Remarks about your granddaughter
might draw attention to you.

10:07.074 --> 10:08.940
As will breaking
that man's hand.

10:08.942 --> 10:10.942
So, why don't you
let go of it now?

10:10.944 --> 10:12.978
Come on,
let go of his hand.

10:15.247 --> 10:17.115
No, lenny, of course not.

10:17.117 --> 10:20.285
How could I possibly
have a granddaughter?

10:20.287 --> 10:22.921
Is that, uh,
joan solodar over there?

10:22.923 --> 10:23.955
From the commercials?

10:23.957 --> 10:25.490
"you can go far
in a solodar car."

10:25.492 --> 10:26.491
She your boss?

10:26.493 --> 10:27.792
She's the owner, yes.

10:27.794 --> 10:29.127
I'd like her
to sell me the car.

10:29.129 --> 10:31.896
[ chuckles ]
ms. Solodar doesn't do sales.

10:31.898 --> 10:33.431
She owns the dealership.

10:33.433 --> 10:34.599
Well, no offense, lenny,

10:34.601 --> 10:36.134
But now I've shaken hands
with a little girl.

10:36.136 --> 10:37.836
I'd like to make a deal
with a real woman.

10:41.741 --> 10:43.575
Alexa, there should be
14 new products

10:43.577 --> 10:45.310
At the new production
presentation,

10:45.312 --> 10:47.646
But I only see 13 new products
on this list.

10:47.648 --> 10:49.080
Why was this one removed?

10:49.082 --> 10:50.815
Mary said she needed it.

10:50.817 --> 10:52.851
Did she say for what?

10:52.853 --> 10:54.552
No, otto, she didn't.

11:06.499 --> 11:08.933
If you want your hat,
sheriff...

11:08.935 --> 11:11.703
You're gonna have to come
and get it.

11:17.643 --> 11:20.111
I think you hurt
lenny's feelings.

11:20.113 --> 11:21.880
I think he'll get over it.

11:21.882 --> 11:24.049
He said
you wanted to see me.

11:24.051 --> 11:26.718
I prefer to do business
with the boss.

11:26.720 --> 11:29.988
I can understand that.

11:29.990 --> 11:33.558
You're a man
who knows what he wants.

11:33.560 --> 11:35.627
I'd like to think so.

11:35.629 --> 11:38.997
That was you selling me,
wasn't it?

11:38.999 --> 11:40.965
You were selling me?

11:40.967 --> 11:43.201
Yes.

11:43.203 --> 11:44.335
I confess.

11:44.337 --> 11:47.572
This is why I don't
do sales anymore.

11:47.574 --> 11:50.408
You gonna send me
back to lenny?

11:50.410 --> 11:52.811
No.

11:55.881 --> 11:57.949
I'm all yours.

12:00.686 --> 12:03.521
Then come on.
Sell me a car.

12:03.523 --> 12:06.357
[ sighs ]

12:06.359 --> 12:10.028
The cockpit is designed
so you have complete control.

12:10.030 --> 12:13.865
Everything is exactly
where you need it to be.

12:13.867 --> 12:17.936
It's tight in the corners,
hugs the road.

12:17.938 --> 12:22.240
And for a luxury car,
it really wants to go.

12:22.242 --> 12:23.408
Lots of power.

12:23.410 --> 12:26.244
The engine
is incredibly responsive.

12:26.246 --> 12:30.148
Just a very light touch...

12:33.252 --> 12:35.887
<i>...And she'll really</i>
<i>open up to you.</i>

12:35.889 --> 12:39.390
I was 25
when my dad made that bust.

12:39.392 --> 12:41.593
Newspaper called him
a hero.

12:41.595 --> 12:45.430
Not sure the mayor would've
given him the key to the city

12:45.432 --> 12:49.300
If he knew about joan solodar
and that body they buried.

12:49.302 --> 12:50.902
Should we take it
for a test-drive?

12:50.904 --> 12:52.937
You know what, actually,
I'm looking for something

12:52.939 --> 12:54.405
With a little more power.

12:54.407 --> 12:56.074
What did you
have in mind?

12:56.076 --> 12:57.208
Heroin.

12:57.210 --> 12:59.711
I know you supply it.

12:59.713 --> 13:02.781
I sell cars, mr. Brown.

13:05.317 --> 13:07.986
I'm not looking to step on
your business in seattle.

13:07.988 --> 13:10.155
I've seen what happens
to people who do.

13:10.157 --> 13:12.457
I want to expand it
into other markets --

13:12.459 --> 13:14.325
Montana, wyoming,
colorado, utah.

13:14.327 --> 13:16.995
They all need
a quality product.

13:16.997 --> 13:20.799
$10 million order
to start.

13:20.801 --> 13:24.803
As much as I like
that number...

13:24.805 --> 13:25.970
I sell cars.

13:25.972 --> 13:30.074
And I have no idea why you think
I did anything else.

13:30.076 --> 13:33.411
Your man over there --
lenny.

13:33.413 --> 13:36.014
I did time with his uncle
in pelican bay.

13:36.016 --> 13:39.117
He told me you sell
more than just cars.

13:39.119 --> 13:42.520
Want to check me out?
Call him.

13:46.659 --> 13:49.294
Mary's never taken
a new product before.

13:49.296 --> 13:53.698
It's always something
we do together.

13:57.136 --> 13:58.703
Where is pritchard?

14:02.141 --> 14:05.210
How's, uh,
how's uncle jack?

14:05.212 --> 14:07.846
Almost ready to go.

14:07.848 --> 14:09.614
Okay.

14:10.950 --> 14:12.317
You sure
this is gonna work?

14:12.319 --> 14:13.785
Arthur:
<i>Yes, agent pritchard.</i>

14:13.787 --> 14:15.520
<i>All the visual</i>
<i>and voice data needed</i>

14:15.522 --> 14:17.021
<i>Was obtained</i>
<i>during the hack</i>

14:17.023 --> 14:19.891
<i>Of lenny's last skype session</i>
<i>with his uncle.</i>

14:31.871 --> 14:33.538
No wires.

14:33.540 --> 14:35.573
He's clean.

14:43.349 --> 14:45.917
Please remember your camera's
in your contact lens.

14:45.919 --> 14:47.952
So do us all a favor
and don't look in the mirror.

15:03.569 --> 15:05.904
This scar
come with a story?

15:08.207 --> 15:10.909
I got it saving
his uncle's ass.

15:10.911 --> 15:12.877
Well, why don't we
ask him about that?

15:12.879 --> 15:15.046
Duval: Lenny...

15:15.048 --> 15:17.348
What are you doing
calling me?

15:17.350 --> 15:18.750
Everything okay
with your mom?

15:18.752 --> 15:20.852
Yeah, everything's fine,
uncle jack.

15:20.854 --> 15:23.321
It's just this guy here
says he knows you.

15:27.893 --> 15:30.795
I have no idea
who that is.

15:30.797 --> 15:31.930
[ gun cocks ]
-uh...

15:31.932 --> 15:34.432
I'm just messing with ya.
That's...

15:34.434 --> 15:35.533
Cameron brown.

15:37.770 --> 15:38.770
[ sighs ]

15:38.772 --> 15:40.471
How you doing, jack?

15:40.473 --> 15:41.739
Not as good as you.

15:41.741 --> 15:43.908
What's going on?

15:43.910 --> 15:46.110
I need you
to vouch for me.

15:49.248 --> 15:51.215
[ static crackling ]

15:53.152 --> 15:54.485
What the hell's
going on?

15:54.487 --> 15:56.955
Otto: That holo-projector
isn't even beta tested.

15:56.957 --> 15:59.390
They were supposed to show it
at today's meeting.

15:59.392 --> 16:00.291
You took it.

16:00.293 --> 16:01.793
Get him to turn it
back on now.

16:01.795 --> 16:03.695
Fix it, please.

16:07.099 --> 16:08.599
It's not on our end.

16:08.601 --> 16:10.034
I don't like this.

16:11.570 --> 16:14.105
You don't come to the meeting,
then you let him use that?

16:14.107 --> 16:16.975
I know you don't like
helping pritchard, but I do.

16:16.977 --> 16:19.143
We can't go
in two directions, mary.

16:19.145 --> 16:21.679
If we go in two directions,
we will pull apart.

16:21.681 --> 16:23.481
You need to turn it
back on now.

16:23.483 --> 16:25.817
My dad is out there
with a gun to his head.

16:25.819 --> 16:27.585
You are gonna turn this
back on now,

16:27.587 --> 16:30.321
Or I am coming down there and
I'm gonna put a gun to yours.

16:35.194 --> 16:36.694
Sorry about that.

16:36.696 --> 16:38.696
Connection here is crap.

16:38.698 --> 16:41.866
I only got a couple of seconds,
but...

16:41.868 --> 16:44.502
I'd trust that man
with my life.

16:46.138 --> 16:47.505
[ laptop chirps ]

16:47.507 --> 16:49.340
So, we all good?

16:49.342 --> 16:51.009
We doing business?

16:51.011 --> 16:53.344
It's time for you to leave,
mr. Brown.

16:53.346 --> 16:55.279
We'll be in touch.

16:55.281 --> 16:57.949
Lenny, show him out.

16:57.951 --> 17:00.785
And then come to bed.

17:12.664 --> 17:15.366
[ sighs ]
did she when she'd call?

17:15.368 --> 17:18.803
I mean, did you sell her
on the deal or not?

17:18.805 --> 17:20.204
You were watching.

17:20.206 --> 17:22.540
Yeah, I was.
But I can't tell.

17:22.542 --> 17:26.010
Unlike you, I don't know her,
know her "moves."

17:26.012 --> 17:28.246
Maybe you two can throw
that ball around outside.

17:28.248 --> 17:30.048
I did like the part
where you said you'd trust me

17:30.050 --> 17:31.082
With your life.

17:31.084 --> 17:32.917
Me?
No, that was uncle jack.

17:32.919 --> 17:35.753
Maybe you two can throw
that ball around outside.

17:35.755 --> 17:37.255
[ cellphone rings ]

17:37.257 --> 17:38.556
Joan: Mr. Brown.

17:38.558 --> 17:40.058
Joan.

17:40.060 --> 17:41.492
If you can prove funds,

17:41.494 --> 17:43.928
I think I have something
to sell you.

17:43.930 --> 17:50.568
Joan solodar
was your father's c.I.?

17:50.570 --> 17:52.703
For the record,
duval didn't know that.

17:52.705 --> 17:54.038
Dad only told that to me.

17:54.040 --> 17:56.574
Because he's the good son
and you're the bad son.

17:56.576 --> 17:58.342
It's what makes me
such a good c.I.

17:58.344 --> 18:01.079
I'm telling you, she's the money
behind the jalisco brothers.

18:01.081 --> 18:03.948
You're asking me
to go after joan solodar,

18:03.950 --> 18:07.051
A clean record,
taxpaying local businesswoman,

18:07.053 --> 18:10.721
Based on the word of a corrupt,
disgraced sheriff?

18:10.723 --> 18:14.225
Yes, ma'am, we are.
I am.

18:14.227 --> 18:16.260
My father may have been
all those things,

18:16.262 --> 18:17.395
But whatever he did,

18:17.397 --> 18:19.097
He did it
for the good of this city.

18:19.099 --> 18:21.265
If he says she's the one
behind that heroin,

18:21.267 --> 18:22.700
Then we need
to act on it.

18:22.702 --> 18:24.402
You want to stop
these drugs.

18:24.404 --> 18:26.771
No, I don't need you
to tell me what I want,

18:26.773 --> 18:28.372
So close up
while I think.

18:30.742 --> 18:31.742
Okay.

18:31.744 --> 18:33.478
I'll get legal to okay
the buy money.

18:33.480 --> 18:35.780
You go back to joan
and set the meet.

18:35.782 --> 18:36.914
You won't regret this.

18:36.916 --> 18:37.982
Said the bad son.

18:50.462 --> 18:53.231
Where are you
meeting her?

18:53.233 --> 18:55.633
Her place.

18:55.635 --> 18:58.102
She's very beautiful.

18:58.104 --> 19:01.439
Mm-hmm.
Suppose so.

19:01.441 --> 19:04.509
Is that how
she fooled you?

19:07.779 --> 19:09.213
[ giggles ]

19:11.617 --> 19:13.284
[ sighs ]

19:13.286 --> 19:15.386
Does duval know?

19:17.322 --> 19:19.223
How you felt
about her?

19:22.027 --> 19:24.996
How did I figure it out?

19:24.998 --> 19:26.664
I'm a woman.

19:26.666 --> 19:29.734
I can tell these things.

19:33.939 --> 19:35.907
You should tell duval.

19:42.548 --> 19:43.948
[ beep ]

19:43.950 --> 19:46.050
[ door buzzes ]

19:46.052 --> 19:47.885
Man: <i>Mr. Brown,</i>

19:47.887 --> 19:49.687
Ms. Solodar's
expecting you.

19:49.689 --> 19:51.556
Go right up
to the penthouse.

20:11.076 --> 20:13.811
[ laughs ]

20:15.747 --> 20:16.781
Hm?

20:23.055 --> 20:24.455
[ elevator dings ]

20:28.760 --> 20:30.995
How you doing,
fellas?

20:30.997 --> 20:32.897
I know you?

20:37.936 --> 20:39.170
100 grand.

20:39.172 --> 20:40.438
Good faith.

20:40.440 --> 20:42.907
Rest when we make a deal.

20:42.909 --> 20:45.409
What you want
comes from mexico.

20:45.411 --> 20:46.577
We import it.

20:46.579 --> 20:48.913
We wanted to see your face
so that you understand

20:48.915 --> 20:50.915
That you're in business
with us now, too.

20:50.917 --> 20:53.951
<i>Things go well,</i>
<i>you don't see us again.</i>

20:53.953 --> 20:57.488
Things go badly,
you'll see us once more.

21:08.767 --> 21:11.602
That was reese.
Put a tail on him, now.

21:13.438 --> 21:15.473
That was smart.

21:15.475 --> 21:18.276
Joan solodar
wasn't in the elevator.

21:18.278 --> 21:20.077
They didn't say her name.

21:20.079 --> 21:23.681
Nothing to put this
on her.

21:27.486 --> 21:29.186
[ elevator dings ]

21:43.835 --> 21:46.070
I hope you had
a pleasant ride up.

21:46.072 --> 21:48.472
I met some interesting people
in the elevator.

21:48.474 --> 21:51.575
Isn't that what we have
to embrace in life?

21:51.577 --> 21:54.745
Unexpected meetings
with interesting people.

22:09.594 --> 22:11.429
What would
your little league team think

22:11.431 --> 22:13.698
About you hanging out
with these cartel hard boys?

22:15.334 --> 22:17.034
What do you think of me?

22:17.036 --> 22:21.272
I think you're a badass,
solly.

22:21.274 --> 22:23.074
Solly...

22:24.509 --> 22:29.680
...Was a nickname I used
a long time ago.

22:31.616 --> 22:34.318
Solodar was a mouthful.

22:34.320 --> 22:37.922
And the last person to call me
that died a while back.

22:40.359 --> 22:43.461
You said your c.I.
Just met her?

22:43.463 --> 22:44.528
Yeah, why?

22:44.530 --> 22:45.996
Because the way they talk,

22:45.998 --> 22:48.199
It kind of seems like
he's doing her.

22:48.201 --> 22:51.135
Seem like that to you?
Like he's getting that?

22:51.137 --> 22:53.671
<i>That is a worrisome</i>
<i>piece of trivia</i>

22:53.673 --> 22:55.606
To know about me,
mr. Brown.

22:56.875 --> 22:58.576
Should I be worried?

23:01.513 --> 23:02.913
I do my homework.

23:02.915 --> 23:05.549
A deal this big, I want to know
everything about a person.

23:05.551 --> 23:08.052
So, what do you know
about me?

23:08.054 --> 23:10.554
I know this business
used to be ray carson's.

23:10.556 --> 23:12.690
And now it belongs to you.

23:12.692 --> 23:15.860
I know you run it
better than ray did.

23:15.862 --> 23:18.829
I know that you keep lenny
around for fun.

23:18.831 --> 23:20.898
You never let him
get close.

23:20.900 --> 23:24.101
I know if you keep heading
that way...

23:24.103 --> 23:27.671
You're gonna be old and alone,
ms. Solodar.

23:27.673 --> 23:29.907
[ chuckles ]

23:32.677 --> 23:34.178
I'm gonna give you
an address,

23:34.180 --> 23:36.480
And you meet me there
in three hours with the cash.

23:39.584 --> 23:42.753
Oh, and please
call me solly.

23:42.755 --> 23:44.922
Makes me feel young.

23:56.568 --> 23:58.369
The building
where she wants to make the deal

23:58.371 --> 23:59.703
Is three blocks
off the harbor.

23:59.705 --> 24:01.439
The coast guard will cover
the water for us.

24:01.441 --> 24:03.607
We'll have one chopper in
the air at a standoff position,

24:03.609 --> 24:04.809
And s.W.A.T.
On the ground.

24:04.811 --> 24:06.076
Woman: Ma'am.

24:06.078 --> 24:08.946
Got a report of shots fired
at solodar motors.

24:15.654 --> 24:17.488
[ police radio chatter ]

24:19.291 --> 24:20.724
Solly.

24:20.726 --> 24:23.127
What about it?

24:23.129 --> 24:25.095
I slipped.

24:25.097 --> 24:26.931
Called her a nickname
I shouldn't have known,

24:26.933 --> 24:27.965
And I thought I covered,

24:27.967 --> 24:29.600
But she made me
when I called her solly.

24:29.602 --> 24:31.969
Why weren't you
supposed to know that name?

24:31.971 --> 24:33.871
I thought I covered.

24:35.607 --> 24:39.677
Lenny was
laundering money

24:39.679 --> 24:42.947
Through the dealership --
drug money.

24:42.949 --> 24:48.652
And when he found out
that I knew, he...

24:48.654 --> 24:50.654
[ crying ]

24:50.656 --> 24:53.491
He tried to kill me.

24:53.493 --> 24:55.726
He came at me.

24:58.663 --> 24:59.597
You stay here.

24:59.599 --> 25:00.664
Duval, listen.

25:00.666 --> 25:02.833
She killed lenny
to get herself cleared,

25:02.835 --> 25:04.502
Just like she did
with ray.

25:04.504 --> 25:06.537
She did it again.

25:06.539 --> 25:21.318
Man: The money was laundered
through the car dealerships,

25:21.320 --> 25:24.021
Which, as you can see
from these corporate records,

25:24.023 --> 25:26.457
Are in lenny wahl's name.

25:26.459 --> 25:28.025
When my client
discovered this --

25:28.027 --> 25:29.326
Joan:
I confronted lenny.

25:29.328 --> 25:30.661
It was stupid, I know.

25:30.663 --> 25:33.697
I should've just gone
to the cops, but I was so mad.

25:35.166 --> 25:36.534
And then he beat me.

25:36.536 --> 25:37.568
The emts on scene

25:37.570 --> 25:39.537
Documented the bruising
on my client's body.

25:39.539 --> 25:41.305
We're prepared
to fully cooperate

25:41.307 --> 25:42.473
With this investigation.

25:42.475 --> 25:43.941
Excuse me for a moment.

25:48.413 --> 25:51.048
Something's going around
in my head

25:51.050 --> 25:52.716
That's been bugging me.

25:52.718 --> 25:55.853
I thought it was that you knew
her nickname.

25:55.855 --> 25:58.188
But it's not
that you knew it.

25:58.190 --> 26:00.724
It was the way you said it
to her,

26:00.726 --> 26:02.826
And what you said
about her.

26:02.828 --> 26:04.428
You were gonna save her!

26:04.430 --> 26:06.430
Five months,
day and night.

26:06.432 --> 26:10.401
I had to move back to the house
because mom couldn't take it.

26:10.403 --> 26:12.436
That's when she started
taking those pills.

26:12.438 --> 26:13.771
Do you know that?
That --

26:13.773 --> 26:16.574
One, there are a lot of things
about me and your mother

26:16.576 --> 26:17.741
That you don't know.

26:17.743 --> 26:19.743
Two is keep
your voice down.

26:19.745 --> 26:21.445
People are listening
to you accuse me

26:21.447 --> 26:22.813
Of things
your father did.

26:26.418 --> 26:28.252
Yeah.
Come on, come on, do it!

26:28.254 --> 26:29.286
Do it!

26:39.598 --> 26:41.532
Excuse me.

26:41.534 --> 26:43.300
[ door opens ]

26:48.139 --> 26:51.141
What the hell
was that about?

26:51.143 --> 26:54.044
Family stuff.

26:54.046 --> 26:56.213
What about her?

26:58.249 --> 27:01.118
She made your c.I.
She walks.

27:04.155 --> 27:06.991
[ sighs ]

27:06.993 --> 27:09.226
[ cellphone rings ]

27:11.796 --> 27:12.796
Hello?

27:12.798 --> 27:14.264
Hey, uh, it's helen.

27:14.266 --> 27:15.799
Now's not a good time,
helen.

27:15.801 --> 27:17.568
I think something might be wrong
with gracie.

27:17.570 --> 27:18.836
She's been staying with me

27:18.838 --> 27:21.005
While duval's been working
on the big heroin case.

27:21.007 --> 27:22.840
I came home,
she's supposed to be here,

27:22.842 --> 27:24.808
She's not,
and she's been seeing this guy.

27:24.810 --> 27:27.411
And I didn't tell duval because
I didn't want to worry him,

27:27.413 --> 27:29.013
And she's not answering
her phone.

27:29.015 --> 27:30.280
S-slow down.

27:30.282 --> 27:33.917
And then there's this,
um, vent that was open,

27:33.919 --> 27:35.419
And -- and there's

27:35.421 --> 27:37.087
This cookie tin inside,
and --

27:37.089 --> 27:38.522
I mean,
the guy's a drummer,

27:38.524 --> 27:40.324
But why worry duval
with that, right?

27:40.326 --> 27:42.026
'cause he just does
so much.
Helen,

27:42.028 --> 27:44.495
The cookie tin,
is there anything in it?

27:44.497 --> 27:46.430
It's, um --
it's -- it's empty.

27:46.432 --> 27:48.165
But, um --
[ sniffs ] god.

27:48.167 --> 27:50.134
It's got a funky smell,
though.

27:50.136 --> 27:51.669
-Yeah.
[ elevator dings ]

27:51.671 --> 27:53.270
Gunpowder.

27:53.272 --> 27:54.438
[ gunshot ]

28:01.880 --> 28:03.180
Okay, that's enough.

28:03.182 --> 28:04.648
It's getting late.

28:04.650 --> 28:05.949
Just a few more.

28:05.951 --> 28:08.686
Have another beer,
gracie-loo-hoo,

28:08.688 --> 28:09.820
While I reload.

28:09.822 --> 28:12.656
Okay, why don't you
give me the gun now?

28:12.658 --> 28:13.791
It's cool.

28:13.793 --> 28:15.626
How'd you know
about this place, anyway?

28:15.628 --> 28:17.594
Her grandfather
took her here.

28:19.197 --> 28:21.465
He trusted her
with what was in that air vent,

28:21.467 --> 28:23.901
And he took her down here
to teach her how to shoot.

28:23.903 --> 28:24.902
It was their secret.

28:24.904 --> 28:26.704
But he told you,
I guess.

28:26.706 --> 28:28.238
What are you doing here?

28:28.240 --> 28:29.907
Come take you home.
Let's go.

28:29.909 --> 28:31.108
She's with me.

28:33.645 --> 28:34.878
Aah!

28:34.880 --> 28:36.714
Car keys, now!

28:36.716 --> 28:37.881
[ keys jingle ]

28:37.883 --> 28:39.817
And if I catch you
hanging around gracie again,

28:39.819 --> 28:41.985
I'm gonna snap your fingers off,
drummer boy.

28:41.987 --> 28:42.986
Gracie, let's go.

28:42.988 --> 28:43.887
No.

28:47.659 --> 28:49.059
How many of these
you had?

28:49.061 --> 28:50.728
None of your business.

28:50.730 --> 28:53.564
Look, I can take care
of myself, okay?

28:53.566 --> 28:54.832
Yeah?

28:54.834 --> 28:58.035
Well, you're still a kid
and you shouldn't have to.

28:58.037 --> 28:59.636
Put me down!

29:04.242 --> 29:05.743
Duval:
Where'd you find her?

29:05.745 --> 29:07.845
I'll let her
tell you that.

29:07.847 --> 29:10.414
But, duval,
she's taking care of you

29:10.416 --> 29:13.016
The way you took care
of your mother.

29:13.018 --> 29:15.619
Maybe gracie
just needs to be gracie.

29:15.621 --> 29:18.188
You're giving me
parenting advice?

29:18.190 --> 29:19.356
That's rich.

29:19.358 --> 29:22.259
Do I even need to remind you
that joan solodar

29:22.261 --> 29:25.262
Walked out of the fbi
with no charges filed?

29:25.264 --> 29:27.765
You remember joan, right?

29:27.767 --> 29:29.767
Helen: Joan solodar?

29:29.769 --> 29:32.169
Didn't daddy
used to buy his cars from her?

29:33.738 --> 29:34.705
Mm-hmm.

29:34.707 --> 29:36.540
Sorry, helen.
Can we talk in private?

29:39.978 --> 29:43.080
Look, if you want to hate me
for what I did,

29:43.082 --> 29:44.448
Join the damn club.

29:44.450 --> 29:46.250
Joan solodar
is still out there.

29:46.252 --> 29:47.618
-Shut up.
-"shut up"?

29:47.620 --> 29:50.254
I don't want to hear you say,
that we can still get her,

29:50.256 --> 29:52.089
That you know her
better than anyone.

29:52.091 --> 29:54.424
I can still be mad at you
all I want,

29:54.426 --> 29:57.094
But you have a plan
to put her behind bars.

29:57.096 --> 29:59.930
That's what you were gonna say,
wasn't it?

29:59.932 --> 30:00.998
Wasn't it?

30:01.000 --> 30:04.168
Well, I was gonna start
with "I'm sorry."

30:04.170 --> 30:07.738
Then I was gonna get
to all that other stuff.

30:07.740 --> 30:11.475
But, duval,
we can still get her.

30:11.477 --> 30:14.645
You remember cory,
the accountant.

30:14.813 --> 30:18.215
â™ª

30:21.920 --> 30:24.254
Hey, you said there
was gonna be a poker game.

30:24.256 --> 30:26.356
Where the hell is it?

30:26.358 --> 30:29.293
I said if you liked poker,
you should come down here.

30:29.295 --> 30:31.495
I never said there
was gonna be a game.

30:31.497 --> 30:35.265
Cory.

30:35.267 --> 30:38.168
Didn't he tell you to stay away
from the coke and cards?

30:38.170 --> 30:40.337
Who are you?
How do you know that?

30:40.339 --> 30:43.507
The same way we know
joan solodar lost a lot of money

30:43.509 --> 30:48.345
Making it look like
lenny ran her drug business.

30:48.347 --> 30:52.282
But she has more money,
doesn't she?

30:55.954 --> 30:58.088
And you know
where it is.

31:01.359 --> 31:03.360
[ ringing ]

31:03.362 --> 31:06.530
Hey, we need to talk
about the money.

31:06.532 --> 31:08.398
The usual place.

31:08.400 --> 31:12.369
Okay, thank you.
I'll be right over.

31:12.371 --> 31:13.704
[ beep ]

31:20.845 --> 31:22.880
Otto, I need
a surveillance system

31:22.882 --> 31:25.682
For an area that's
too heavily wooded for a drone.

31:25.684 --> 31:26.884
With the biometrics?

31:26.886 --> 31:29.486
For what you're doing
with pritchard?
Yes.

31:29.488 --> 31:32.055
I didn't bring him back
so you could help him atone

31:32.057 --> 31:33.056
For his past sins.

31:33.058 --> 31:37.027
You brought him back
to save my life.

31:37.029 --> 31:39.396
But it's my life, otto.

31:39.398 --> 31:43.901
I like it out there.
It makes me happy.

31:43.903 --> 31:46.236
Don't you want that?

31:46.238 --> 31:49.573
It makes you happy
because of what you're doing...

31:49.575 --> 31:52.943
Or who you're
doing it with?

31:52.945 --> 31:56.513
You can't be with him,
mary.

31:56.515 --> 31:58.916
He's our experiment.

31:58.918 --> 32:00.784
You know that.

32:19.103 --> 32:20.270
Arthur?

32:20.272 --> 32:21.605
Arthur: <i>Yes, otto.</i>

32:21.607 --> 32:24.441
We need to start a search
for a new donor

32:24.443 --> 32:27.210
With the same precursor
as pritchard's.

32:27.212 --> 32:28.779
<i>But, otto, as a donor,</i>

32:28.781 --> 32:31.581
<i>Mr. Pritchard</i>
<i>is performing perfectly.</i>

32:31.583 --> 32:32.616
I know.

32:32.618 --> 32:34.785
<i>Mary's cancer</i>
<i>is in remission,</i>

32:34.787 --> 32:37.754
<i>But ongoing therapy</i>
<i>is still required.</i>

32:37.756 --> 32:40.924
Just find another donor
like I told you to.

32:40.926 --> 32:44.728
<i>Other than the donor</i>
<i>you already know about?</i>

32:47.932 --> 32:50.567
If joan takes duval's bait,
then we have her.

32:50.569 --> 32:53.136
She really did
a number on you.

32:53.138 --> 32:56.974
I did a number on me
all by myself.

32:56.976 --> 32:58.642
You sure
that thing will work?

32:58.644 --> 33:02.612
It's a genuine
lookinglass product.

33:02.614 --> 33:05.148
It tracks the heartbeats
of anyone out there.

33:06.818 --> 33:09.386
Right now,
it's reading three.

33:24.669 --> 33:27.504
I thought you were
coming alone.

33:39.117 --> 33:41.818
So, you're the son?

33:41.820 --> 33:44.588
Jimmy's golden boy?

33:46.991 --> 33:49.926
Oh, yeah,
I heard all about you.

33:52.230 --> 33:54.965
He'd go on and on.

33:58.036 --> 33:59.369
It's been a long time

33:59.371 --> 34:03.040
Since I've had my hands
on a pritchard.

34:04.909 --> 34:07.244
You know, your dad
had that anger in him

34:07.246 --> 34:08.378
That made bedtime

34:08.380 --> 34:10.447
Real special.

34:12.817 --> 34:14.985
Am I feeling
some of that in you?

34:21.759 --> 34:24.327
No wires.

34:24.329 --> 34:27.564
You're gonna hear a lot worse
about me before we're done here.

34:27.566 --> 34:30.400
You were
a different person then.

34:30.402 --> 34:33.236
Maybe.

34:33.238 --> 34:36.373
But I'm still on the hook
for what I've done, aren't I?

34:36.375 --> 34:39.409
You, go first.
Speak quickly.

34:39.411 --> 34:41.912
If the fbi knows about the money
I shielded for you,

34:41.914 --> 34:44.081
They know everything
wasn't in lenny's name.

34:44.083 --> 34:46.616
The fbi doesn't
know anything.

34:46.618 --> 34:49.619
He's out here
without official cover.

34:49.621 --> 34:53.190
God, cory, you really
are a bad poker player.

34:53.192 --> 34:55.992
He bluffed you,
and you told him.

34:58.062 --> 34:59.930
[ scoffs ]

34:59.932 --> 35:03.233
So, what do you want?

35:03.235 --> 35:06.536
I know you fooled my father
into setting you up in business,

35:06.538 --> 35:08.872
And he ruined
my mother's life doing it.

35:08.874 --> 35:11.141
I want you to pay me
for that.

35:11.143 --> 35:14.644
I made a calculation --
five months, day and night.

35:14.646 --> 35:18.215
I put a dollar amount
for every hour of those days

35:18.217 --> 35:20.117
He didn't come home.

35:20.119 --> 35:23.186
You're gonna pay me
for that.

35:25.089 --> 35:28.325
And what if I don't?

35:28.327 --> 35:31.695
Then I bring him back
to the fbi.

35:33.464 --> 35:35.065
If she goes for it,
you got her.

35:40.471 --> 35:45.075
You were, what,
25 when he worked that case?

35:47.111 --> 35:49.479
And you had to move
back home

35:49.481 --> 35:52.449
Because it took a toll
on your mommy.

35:52.451 --> 35:54.317
<i>Yeah,</i>
<i>I know about that, too.</i>

35:54.319 --> 35:56.353
Why would she turn her back
on them?

35:56.355 --> 35:57.521
[ device chirps ]

35:57.523 --> 35:59.890
Three more heartbeats,
20 yards away.

36:04.695 --> 36:06.496
Your dad called her,
though,

36:06.498 --> 36:08.865
On those nights
he wasn't gonna get home.

36:08.867 --> 36:12.269
He made those calls
from my bed.

36:27.852 --> 36:30.687
You're not like him.

36:30.689 --> 36:34.524
You're soft.

36:34.526 --> 36:36.560
Or good.

36:36.562 --> 36:39.129
What's the difference?

36:44.702 --> 36:46.403
I'm not like him.

36:48.039 --> 36:51.241
He was stupid
to let you use him.

36:52.810 --> 36:55.679
I just want to get paid.

36:55.681 --> 36:57.414
Last chance.

37:00.685 --> 37:01.651
[ grunts ]

37:01.653 --> 37:05.722
[ chuckles ]
you want to be bad?

37:05.724 --> 37:07.490
You want to be like
your father?

37:09.260 --> 37:10.627
Make that go away.

37:11.729 --> 37:13.563
Where do you think
you're going?

37:13.565 --> 37:15.699
I'm gonna walk
a little ways over here

37:15.701 --> 37:17.834
And put the two of you
in the ground

37:17.836 --> 37:19.903
Where I put ray
after I killed him.

37:22.740 --> 37:24.174
James: I can't find
the other two men.

37:24.176 --> 37:27.077
<i>Where are the heartbeats</i>
<i>coming from?</i>

37:27.079 --> 37:30.680
You think it's easy being
a woman in the drug business?

37:30.682 --> 37:35.452
I built up this business up.
I earned this money.

37:35.454 --> 37:38.021
And no pritchard,
living or dead,

37:38.023 --> 37:40.523
Is gonna take that
away from me.

37:49.100 --> 37:50.967
How you doing, solly?

37:53.104 --> 37:55.205
[ device beeps ]

37:55.207 --> 37:56.606
[ computer dings ]

38:01.712 --> 38:03.747
Duval: <i>Where do you think</i>
<i>you're going?</i>

38:03.749 --> 38:05.782
<i>I'm gonna walk</i>
<i>a little ways over here</i>

38:05.784 --> 38:07.751
And put the two of you
<i>in the ground</i>

38:07.753 --> 38:10.287
<i>Where I put ray</i>
<i>after I killed him.</i>

38:10.289 --> 38:14.791
You think it's easy being
a woman in the drug business?

38:14.793 --> 38:18.762
I built this business up.
<i>I earned that money.</i>

38:18.764 --> 38:21.398
<i>And no pritchard,</i>
<i>living or dead,</i>

38:21.400 --> 38:23.967
<i>Is gonna take that</i>
<i>away from me.</i>

38:23.969 --> 38:27.971
Who are you, really?

38:27.973 --> 38:29.272
Tell me.

38:29.274 --> 38:33.243
Don't open a door unless
you're ready to walk through it.

38:33.245 --> 38:35.378
[ handcuffs click ]

38:46.090 --> 38:48.992
[ police radio chatter ]

38:54.632 --> 38:57.200
Got a question for you.

39:00.338 --> 39:02.505
Shoot.

39:02.507 --> 39:06.142
Why'd you do it?

39:06.144 --> 39:08.278
[ sighs ]

39:08.280 --> 39:12.215
I was about your age.

39:12.217 --> 39:14.784
My youth was behind me.

39:14.786 --> 39:18.188
I could see
what was coming.

39:18.190 --> 39:19.856
She was young.

39:19.858 --> 39:23.460
She -- she made me
feel young.

39:25.496 --> 39:27.330
And I made
a mess of things.

39:27.332 --> 39:29.666
Yeah.

39:29.668 --> 39:32.702
You did.

39:32.704 --> 39:35.105
I'm trying
to fix things now.

39:39.343 --> 39:41.378
I'd like to believe
you are.

39:44.181 --> 39:45.348
What -- what --

39:45.350 --> 39:48.418
What do you mean
you'd "like" to believe me?

39:48.420 --> 39:50.920
[ car door closes,
engine starts ]

39:50.922 --> 39:53.990
Duval, didn't you see
what we just did here?

39:53.992 --> 39:57.494
No, I don't want to hear
you'd "like" to believe me.

39:57.496 --> 40:00.430
You better believe me!

40:06.937 --> 40:09.906
Life is messy, gracie.

40:09.908 --> 40:11.641
That's what I told her.

40:13.344 --> 40:18.014
But we do the best we can,
and...

40:18.016 --> 40:22.752
We forgive each other
when we come up short.

40:22.754 --> 40:23.720
Okay?

40:23.722 --> 40:27.924
Yeah. Okay.

40:27.926 --> 40:30.760
And you know you can't see
that boy anymore.

40:30.762 --> 40:32.695
What?

40:32.697 --> 40:34.731
You can't see him anymore.

40:34.733 --> 40:38.268
No, you can't tell me
who I can see.

40:38.270 --> 40:40.870
Wait. Gracie --
gracie, come back here.

40:40.872 --> 40:41.805
Gracie!

40:41.807 --> 40:43.773
No, you can't tell me
what to do!

40:43.775 --> 40:45.175
Honey, I'm trying --

40:47.445 --> 40:50.880
Arthur, what's the status on
the replacement for pritchard?

40:50.882 --> 40:52.615
Arthur: <i>There is no need</i>
<i>to replace mr. Pritchard.</i>

40:52.617 --> 40:54.083
<i>Mary has the results,</i>

40:54.085 --> 40:57.253
But I was verifying the numbers
<i>before informing you.</i>

40:57.255 --> 40:58.621
Informing me of what?

41:06.330 --> 41:07.230
Mary?

41:07.232 --> 41:08.965
What -- what's wrong?

41:08.967 --> 41:10.300
What happened?

41:10.302 --> 41:13.670
Nothing's wrong.

41:13.672 --> 41:17.974
It's just that, um...

41:17.976 --> 41:19.476
Your blood...

41:21.579 --> 41:23.746
It worked.

41:27.818 --> 41:29.486
I'm cured.

41:29.488 --> 41:30.987
Cured?

41:34.458 --> 41:37.227
[ laughs ]

41:38.996 --> 41:41.097
<i>Her system</i>
<i>is clear of cancer.</i>

41:41.099 --> 41:43.600
<i>There is no need</i>
<i>for further treatment.</i>

41:43.602 --> 41:46.369
<i>May I ask what will we do</i>
<i>with mr. Pritchard?</i>

41:46.371 --> 41:48.204
He'll be leaving.

42:30.481 --> 42:31.981
<i>You've just watched</i>
<i>second chance.</i>

42:31.983 --> 42:35.118
Now here are a few more shows
to check out from fox.

42:36.387 --> 42:38.321
Welcome to the toughest
challenge of your life.

42:38.323 --> 42:40.690
<i>Four decorated heroes--</i>

42:40.692 --> 42:42.325
(trigger cocks,
gunshot)

42:42.327 --> 42:44.394
Will train 16 civilians--

42:44.396 --> 42:46.563
-(horn blows)
-whoo!

42:46.565 --> 42:48.531
Just like they were military.

42:48.533 --> 42:50.867
Let's go!
Get down here now!

42:50.869 --> 42:53.202
-John cena hosts
<i>a team competition--</i>
<i>-all: Booyah!</i>

42:53.204 --> 42:55.905
Where you're only as strong
as your weakest link.

42:55.907 --> 42:57.340
We would have been better off
without you there.

42:57.342 --> 42:59.275
<i>-You give up--</i>
<i>-I'm-a stop this now.</i>

42:59.277 --> 43:00.777
You will be pushed!

43:00.779 --> 43:03.212
-You go home.
-Woman: No, no, no!

43:03.214 --> 43:05.915
American grit. <i>April 14 on fox.</i>

43:07.585 --> 43:10.086
We all got it comin' to us
sooner or later.

43:10.088 --> 43:13.022
Why don't you tell me
about these chains--
how we're gonna break 'em.

43:13.024 --> 43:16.492
Next time I see you,
I will kill you.

43:17.061 --> 43:19.295
â™ª (hip-hop)

43:19.297 --> 43:21.097
Truth is, we are at war.

43:21.099 --> 43:22.198
Drop 'em!

43:22.967 --> 43:24.400
Help me, god!

43:24.402 --> 43:26.636
This whole thing
will bring out
the worst in you.

43:26.638 --> 43:28.771
I want revenge.

43:28.773 --> 43:30.773
We did
what we had to do.
No doubt.
